# Copy to /etc/meetingbox/panel-xrandr.env (install-gdm-kiosk-session.sh does this once).
# Applied at the start of meetingbox-gdm-kiosk-session via apply-kiosk-display-orientation.sh.
# Run `xrandr` on the device to see output names (e.g. DSI-1, HDMI-1, eDP-1).
#
# Rotation not applying? Wrong OUT/mode, or X not ready at login (script retries). See SETUP_PANEL_TOUCH.md.
# MEETINGBOX_PANEL_OUTPUT=auto   # first "connected" output from xrandr
# MEETINGBOX_XRANDR_ATTEMPTS=45
# MEETINGBOX_XRANDR_RETRY_DELAY=1

MEETINGBOX_PANEL_OUTPUT=DSI-1
MEETINGBOX_PANEL_MODE=800x1280
MEETINGBOX_PANEL_ROTATE=right

# --- Rotate LEFT instead (90° CCW): change BOTH lines below, and use touch preset left ---
# MEETINGBOX_PANEL_ROTATE=left
# MEETINGBOX_TOUCH_MATRIX_PRESET=left
# (Equivalent explicit matrix, if you prefer not to use the preset:)
# MEETINGBOX_TOUCH_COORD_MATRIX="0 -1 1 1 0 0 0 0 1"

# --- UI upside down (180°): use inverted for BOTH panel and touch ---
# MEETINGBOX_PANEL_ROTATE=inverted
# MEETINGBOX_TOUCH_MATRIX_PRESET=inverted
# MEETINGBOX_TOUCH_COORD_MATRIX="-1 0 1 0 -1 1 0 0 1"

# After rotation, map touchscreen to the same output (fixes misaligned / dead touch).
# Set to 0 only if you use a mouse-only setup.
MEETINGBOX_MAP_TOUCH_TO_OUTPUT=1

# Best for duplicate names (e.g. Goodix pointer id=15 vs keyboard id=18): use numeric id
# MEETINGBOX_TOUCH_XINPUT_ID=15
#
# Or set the exact name from: xinput list --name-only
# (example for ILITEK panels — use your line verbatim):
# MEETINGBOX_TOUCH_XINPUT_DEVICE='ILITEK ILITEK-TP'
# Multiple devices (pipe-separated):
# MEETINGBOX_TOUCH_XINPUT_NAMES='first touchscreen|second device name'
#
# If the picture is correct but taps land in the wrong place, try a matrix (after map-to-output).
# With no MEETINGBOX_TOUCH_* matrix/preset set, meetingbox-apply-kiosk-display-orientation applies
# the same rotation as MEETINGBOX_PANEL_ROTATE to the touch device. Set MEETINGBOX_TOUCH_MATRIX_PRESET=normal
# if map-to-output alone was enough and an extra matrix makes taps worse.
# Preset should match panel rotation: right ↔ MEETINGBOX_PANEL_ROTATE=right, left ↔ rotate left.
# If taps are ~90° wrong (e.g. button at bottom-center only works when tapping left-center): try the
# OTHER of left/right first, then: MEETINGBOX_TOUCH_MATRIX_PRESET=swap_xy
# MEETINGBOX_TOUCH_MATRIX_PRESET=right
# MEETINGBOX_TOUCH_MATRIX_PRESET=left
# Alternatives: inverted, normal, swap_xy
# Or set nine numbers yourself (overrides preset). Right:  "0 1 0 -1 0 1 0 0 1"
#                                              Left:   "0 -1 1 1 0 0 0 0 1"
#                                              Swap X/Y: "0 1 0 1 0 0 0 0 1"
# MEETINGBOX_TOUCH_COORD_MATRIX="0 1 0 -1 0 1 0 0 1"

# Set to 1 to skip applying xrandr (e.g. desktop monitor debugging):
# MEETINGBOX_SKIP_PANEL_XRANDR=1
